SIMPLE: interrupter
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Interrupter
<hw>In`ter*rupt"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One
who, or that which, interrupts.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Elec.)</fld> <def>A device for opening and closing
an electrical circuit; a vibrating spring or tuning fork, arranged to
make and break a circuit at rapidly recurring intervals, by the action
of the current itself.</def> <altsp>[Also spelled
<asp>interruptor</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Interruption</ent>⟦br⟧
